Assign topic tags to each section of a school document.

For each section, assign 1–5 tags in kebab-case describing the policy area or topic.

Tag vocabulary guidance:
- Use general, reusable tags that will apply consistently across multiple school documents
- Good examples: dress-code, medication-policy, safeguarding, child-protection, trips-and-outings, behaviour-policy, attendance, health-and-safety, mobile-phones, data-protection, communication, fees-and-payments, admissions
- Avoid overly specific tags like "handbook-section-3" or overly broad tags like "school-rules"
- Sections covering the same topic from different angles should share the common tag AND each have a distinguishing tag. For example, student dress code and staff dress code both get "dress-code", and also get "students" and "staff" respectively
- Prefer existing tag vocabulary over inventing new terms for the same concept

Return one entry per section, in the same order as the input list.

